Package: claude-desktop-bin
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, electron | electron-bin | electron33
Recommends: libnotify-bin
Suggests: xdotool, scrot, xclip, wmctrl, xrandr, socat, hyprland, ydotool, grim, slurp, wl-clipboard, wlr-randr, nodejs
Description: Claude AI Desktop Application
 Claude is an AI assistant created by Anthropic to be helpful,
 harmless, and honest. This desktop application provides native
 access to Claude with features including:
 .
  * Conversational AI assistance
  * Code generation and analysis
  * Document understanding
  * Quick Entry for fast access
  * System tray integration
 .
 Optional dependencies for Computer Use (X11/XWayland sessions):
  * xdotool - Input automation + Quick Entry cursor positioning
  * scrot - Screenshot capture
  * xclip - Clipboard access
  * wmctrl - Running app detection
  * xrandr - Display enumeration
 .
 Optional dependencies for Computer Use (Wayland sessions):
  * ydotool - Input automation
  * grim - Screenshot capture (wlroots compositors)
  * slurp - Region selection
  * wl-clipboard - Clipboard access
  * wlr-randr - Display enumeration (wlroots compositors)
  * hyprland - Cursor positioning and window queries (Hyprland only)
 .
 Other optional dependencies:
  * socat - Cowork socket health check in launcher
  * nodejs - For third-party MCP servers requiring system Node.js
 .
 Note: This is an unofficial Linux port of the official Claude
 Desktop application. Requires an Anthropic account to use.
